WILLIAMS, Respondent, v. BRITTANNICA PUB. CO., Appellant. (City Court of New York,

General Term.

June 19, 1893.) Action by Ramon V. Williams against the Brittannica Publishing Company.

Argued before McGÓWN, VAN WYCK, and FITZSIMONS, JJ. *

Smith & White, for appellant. S. Mallet Prevost, for respondent. FITZSIMONS, J.

Finding no meritorious objection to the judgment herein, it is affirmed, with costs.
